      "name": "Ascent V2 — Gauntlet Detail Active Mobile Calibration",
      "context": "Synthetic active-gauntlet mobile calibration derived from the accepted desktop active detail. ORBITAL BLITZ has four qualifier windows, Qualifier 2 open, two scheduled stages, signed-in pilot KITE-07, and Qualifier 2 standings selected. ASCENSION is shown only as the planned optional gauntlet/default race-mode value; if that future field is absent, the gauntlet-level race-mode label is omitted rather than inferred from stage data. No bracket, sponsors, prizes or rewards, broadcast, recent-match heat breakdown, or creator/admin controls. At approximately 320px metadata rows wrap vertically, circuit runtime moves below course names, and the personal stat grid becomes one column if labels no longer fit. No required content is removed. No horizontal page scrolling. Respect reduced motion; provide visible keyboard focus; icons have accessible names; color is never the sole state indicator.",
